        "text": "I <https:\/\/github.com\/h3poteto\/whalebird-desktop\/pull\/5028|implemented> \"Followed hashtags in the sidebar\" feature in the Whalebird desktop client for Mastodon.\n\n<@UC2A2ARPT> If this feature were to be implemented in people's favorite mastodon client apps, it could make mastodon a reasonably good choice for our community. Good thing is that this is a client-only change. API to get a user's followed hashtags already exist in all the client apps.\n\nHere are the relevant discussions for two other client apps. TBH it could be a while for these to move forward, but would be much easier in forks like Hometown:\n• Mastodon web UI: <https:\/\/github.com\/mastodon\/mastodon\/issues\/20802>\n• Elk: <https:\/\/github.com\/elk-zone\/elk\/issues\/1866>",
